{
  "texts": [
    "The return forecast error penalty has a nice interpretation as an uncertainty-weighted leverage.",
    "When the portfolio is long-only, so w ≥ 0, the worst-case asset returns are obvious: they simply take their minimum values, µ -ρ.",
    "In this case the worst-case portfolio mean return (16) is the usual mean portfolio return, with each nominal asset return reduced by its uncertainty.",
    "The return forecast uncertainties ρ can be chosen by several methods.",
    "One simple method is to set all entries the same, and equal to some quantile of the entries of |µ|, such as the 20th percentile."
  ]
}